KING: DEFENDER of the F AlTH.

MOST SERENE KING, The heart of animals is the basis of their

life, the principle of the whole, the Sun of their Microcosm, that upon which all movement dependS, from which all strength proceeds. The King in like

manner is the basis o his Kingdom, the Sun of his World, the heart of the Commonwealth, whence all power derives, all grace appears. What Ihave here written of the movements of the heart I am the more emboldened to present to your Majesty, accord- ing to the Custom of the present age, because nearly all things human are done after human examples and many things in a King are after the pattern of the heart. The Knowledge of his heart therefore will not be useless to a King as embracing akind of Divine
